BT 1 0 0 1 0 43.3 Tm /F1 9.5 Tf 13.2 TL (The Job Shop Scheduling Problem is a compact way to explain one of the hardest practical realities in operations:) Tj T* (every job follows a route, every machine can process only one operation at a time, and every local sequencing choice) Tj T* (can create downstream congestion. The objective in this repository is makespan minimization: finish the last operation) Tj T* (as early as possible while respecting job-precedence and machine-capacity constraints.) Tj T* ET
